(20, 'Apple', 'New York, NY', 'Senior Software Engineer - Apple Services Engineering, Commerce', '&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px; caret-color: rgb(45, 45, 45); color: rgb(45, 45, 45); font-family: &amp;quot;Noto Sans&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Apple Services Engineering team is one of the most exciting examples of Apple&rsquo;s long-held passion for combining art and technology. These are the people who power the App Store, Apple TV, Apple Music, Apple Podcasts, and Apple Books. And they do it on a massive scale, meeting Apple&rsquo;s high expectations with high performance to deliver a huge variety of entertainment in over 35 languages to more than 150 countries. These engineers build secure, end-to-end solutions. They develop the custom software used to process all the creative work, the tools that providers use to deliver that media, all the server-side systems, and the APIs for many Apple services. Thanks to Apple&rsquo;s outstanding integration of hardware, software, and services, engineers here partner to get behind a single unified vision. That vision always includes a deep dedication to strengthening Apple&rsquo;s privacy policy, one of Apple&rsquo;s core values. Although services are a bigger part of Apple&rsquo;s business than ever before, these teams remain small, flexible, and multi-functional, offering greater exposure to the array of opportunities here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;font-size: 16px; font-family: &amp;quot;Noto Sans&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; caret-color: rgb(45, 45, 45); color: rgb(45, 45, 45);&quot;&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;font-size: 16px; font-family: &amp;quot;Noto Sans&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; caret-color: rgb(45, 45, 45); color: rgb(45, 45, 45);&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: 16px; font-family: &amp;quot;Noto Sans&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quo